info.name: SURPARCEL API #Reference
info.description:
# Introduction

This workspace contains examples of requests for operations available on the Surparcel Portal!

To make requests using the Surparcel API, you will need to obtain OAuth client credentials through your user dashboard on the [Surparcel Portal](https://surparcel.com/get-client-credentials). This area of the user dashboard is restricted to clients who are not companies. So, be mindful of this when obtaining your client credentials.

# Obtaining Credentials

#### **Step 1:**

The first step is to request your Company account with Surparcel.

#### **Step 2:**

Once you have your username and password for the Surparcel Portal account, you will be able to obtain your client credentials - Client ID and Client Secret - which will be used to request an access token for the API.

#### **Step 3:**

There are four variables configured for this collection that can be accessed from any endpoints within it.

| **Variable** | **Description** |
| --- | --- |
| username | Email from your Surparcel Account. |
| password | Password from your Surparcel Account. |
| client_id | Client ID (string - uuid) generated with your Surparcel Company account. |
| client_secret | Client Secret(string) generated with your Surparcel Company account. |

Set your own credentials before starting to work with the endpoints in this collection. A post-request script automatically adds a token (after being obtained using the OAuth Grant Password authentication flow) as a collection variable.

## ðŸ’¡Swagger Documentation

[API documentation](https://sur.gafit.com.br/api/documentation)

request.description:
This is a GET request and it is used to "get" data from an endpoint. There is no request body for a GET request, but you can use query parameters to help specify the resource you want data on (e.g., in this request, we have `id=1`).

A successful GET response will have a `200 OK` status, and should include some kind of response body - for example, HTML web content or JSON data.
